    {
      "id": 12,
      "name": "deepMerge",
      "variant": "declaration",
      "kind": 64,
      "flags": {},
      "sources": [
        {
          "fileName": "deep-merge.ts",
          "line": 54,
          "character": 16,
          "url": "https://github.com/ancyloce/anvilkit-studio/blob/main/packages/utils/src/deep-merge.ts#L54"
        }
      ],
      "signatures": [
        {
          "id": 13,
          "name": "deepMerge",
          "variant": "signature",
          "kind": 4096,
          "flags": {},
          "comment": {
            "summary": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Deeply merges one or more "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "`sources`"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " onto "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "`target`"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ", returning a **new**\nobject. The original "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "`target`"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " is never mutated — callers can treat the\nresult as an immutable snapshot.\n\nSemantics:\n\n- Later sources override earlier sources (total order).\n- Plain objects are merged recursively.\n- **Arrays are replaced, not concatenated.** This is the correct\n  behavior for layered configuration (you want Layer 3 to fully\n  override Layer 1's array, not append to it). Other Puck-adjacent\n  codebases have regressed here; do not change it without updating\n  every caller.\n- Non-plain objects (class instances, "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "`Date`"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ", "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "`Map`"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ", "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "`Set`"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ", etc.) are\n  assigned by reference — they are leaf values.\n- Own-property keys "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "`__proto__`"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ", "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "`constructor`"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ", and "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "`prototype`"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " are\n  silently skipped to block prototype-pollution attacks."
              }
            ],
            "blockTags": [
              {
                "tag": "@returns",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "A new "
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "code",
                    "text": "`T`"
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": " containing the merged result."
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "tag": "@example",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "kind": "code",
                    "text": "```ts\ndeepMerge(\n  { theme: { mode: \"light\", tokens: { primary: \"#000\" } } },\n  { theme: { mode: \"dark\" } },\n);\n// => { theme: { mode: \"dark\", tokens: { primary: \"#000\" } } }\n```"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "tag": "@example",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "\n\n"
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "code",
                    "text": "```ts\ndeepMerge({ tags: [\"a\", \"b\"] }, { tags: [\"c\"] });\n// => { tags: [\"c\"] }   // arrays are replaced, not merged\n```"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          "sources": [
            {
              "fileName": "deep-merge.ts",
              "line": 54,
              "character": 16,
              "url": "https://github.com/ancyloce/anvilkit-studio/blob/main/packages/utils/src/deep-merge.ts#L54"
            }
          ],
          "typeParameters": [
            {
              "id": 14,
              "name": "T",
              "variant": "typeParam",
              "kind": 131072,
              "flags": {}
            }
          ],
          "parameters": [
            {
              "id": 15,
              "name": "target",
              "variant": "param",
              "kind": 32768,
              "flags": {},
              "comment": {
                "summary": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "The base value. If it is a plain object, it is\n  shallow-cloned before merging."
                  }
                ]
              },
              "type": {
                "type": "reference",
                "target": 14,
                "name": "T",
                "package": "@anvilkit/utils",
                "refersToTypeParameter": true
              }
            },
            {
              "id": 16,
              "name": "sources",
              "variant": "param",
              "kind": 32768,
              "flags": {
                "isRest": true
              },
              "comment": {
                "summary": [
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "Patches applied in order. "
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "code",
                    "text": "`undefined`"
                  },
                  {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": " sources are\n  ignored so callers can pass optional layers without guarding."
                  }
                ]
              },
              "type": {
                "type": "typeOperator",
                "operator": "readonly",
                "target": {
